Comparing models

Source: R/compare_models.R
compare_models.Rd

Comparing models

Usage

compare_models(models, model_names = NULL)

Arguments

models

an object containing the results returned by a model fitting function. Supported models are 'lm' & 'sfa', put multiple models in list

model_names

vector of model names as string

Value

dataframe of compared models and list for individual models

Examples


mod1 <- lm(Volume ~ Girth + Height, data = datasets::trees)
mod2 <- lm(Volume ~ Girth , data = datasets::trees)
# Comparing models
compare_models(list(mod1, mod2))$compare
#>          term               mod_1               mod_2
#> 1 (Intercept) -57.9877(8.6382)*** -36.9435(3.3651)***
#> 2       Girth   4.7082(0.2643)***   5.0659(0.2474)***
#> 3      Height    0.3393(0.1302)**                    
#> 4         rsq               0.948              0.9353
#> 5     adj_rsq              0.9442              0.9331
#> 6      f_stat         254.9723***         419.3603***
compare_models(mod2)
